{
    "identity": "nprot-177",
    "title": "Mitochondrial respiration measurement",
    "content": [
        {
            "header": "Introduction",
            "content": "Mitochondrial respiration measurement modified for _Drosophila_."
        },
        {
            "header": "Procedure",
            "content": "1)  Isolate mitochondria by gently crushing 40 to 80 flies in a 10 ml Kontes homogenizer with 7 strokes of the pestle in 3 ml homogenization buffer consisting of 225 mM mannitol, 75 mM sucrose, 10 mM MOPS, 1 mM EGTA, 0.5% BSA, pH 7.2 at 4\u00b0C 38. \r\n\n\n2)  Filter the extracts through 8 layers of cheese cloth, and then centrifuge at 300 x G for 3 min in a Beckman Avantis-J25. \r\n\n\n3)  Centrifuge the supernatant at 6000 x G for 10 min to obtain a mitochondrial pellet. \r\n\n\n4)  Measure the mitochondrial protein concentration by the Bradford method, using Bio-Rad reagents, corrected for the BSA content in the homogenization buffer. \r\n\n\n5)  Determine the respiration rates by measuring oxygen consumption using a Clark-type electrode and metabolic chamber containing 0.65 ml of reaction buffer consisting of 225 mM mannitol, 75 mM sucrose, 10 mM KCl, 10 mM Tris-HCl, 5 mM KH\n2\nPO\n4\n, pH 7.2 at 25\u00b0C. \r\n\n\n6)  Calculate the mitochondrial ATP production rates from ADP consumption rates during state III respiration."
        }
    ],
